              <b>TDBA – Privacy Policy</b>
              <br/>
              We collect information of those who applied membership with us, aggregate information on when you register, subscribe to our services, post on our forum, and any information volunteered by the member (such as survey information and site registrations). The collected information will only be used to improve the content of the website and services offered by TDBA. The association will also display your name on the website on the membership page. However other information gathered will not be shared unless if granted with your permission or under the following situation:
              <ul>
                <li>
                  The information is needed in order to prevent, investigate, or take action in any illegal activities, violation of Membership Agreement, and required by the law.
                </li>
              </ul>
              <br/>
              <b>Cookies</b>
              <br/>
              A cookie is a small amount of data, which often includes an anonymous unique identifier that is sent and store on your internet browser that allows your internet browser and the association’s website to communicate.
              <br/>
              Cookies are required to use the TDBA service.
              <br/>
              Cookies lets TDBA to record anonymous information, and not to determine individual activity including the type of the Internet browser, computer’s operating system, website and the areas you have visited prior to our website, and your IP Address.
              <br/>
              <br/>
              The purpose of the cookies including but not limited to the following:
              <ul>
                <li type="a">
                  Provide on target and relevant advertisement
                </li>
                <li type="a">
                  Customize features of the website
                </li>
                <li type="a">
                   Make filling out forms easier
                </li>
                <li type="a">
                  Recognize member once the member have returned to our website
                </li>
                <li type="a">
                  Optimize our website and improve services
                </li>
                <li type="a">
                  Keep track of other websites that refer to our website
                </li>
              </ul>
              <br/>
              <b>Data Storage</b>
              <br/>
              TDBA uses third-party partners to provide the necessary software, required for data storage. The data collected will be recorded in the cloud, Heroku Server, from the United States of America (USA).  The submission of any information means that you agree to the means of storage. All the data will be treated with outmost security and will abide the privacy policy.
              <br/>
              <br/>
              The chosen password that enables you to gain access to the website will be under your responsibility and supervision.  The association strongly suggest you not to share your password to anyone.
              <br/>
              <br/>
              Please note that the process of storing the data through internet is not completely secured. TDBA will do all the necessary precaution and protection for all the data collected, however there is no guarantee for the storage and thus this will be at your own risk.
              <br/>
              <br/>
              <b>Uses of Data</b>
              <br/>
              TDBA will use the data for the following purpose:
              <br/>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  The data will ensure that the content is presented effectively on your computer
                </li>
                <li>
                  To inform all the members about the new or changes to TDBA services
                </li>
                <li>
                  To activate your participation on different interactive features of our services
                </li>
                <li>
                  To guarantee our obligations from any agreements between the member and TDBA
                </li>
                <li>
                  To keep the members abreast to TDBA events, committee meetings, and other similar events
                </li>
              </ul>
              <br/>
              <b>Disclosure</b>
              <br/>
              TDBA may disclose personally identifiable information under special circumstances, such as:
              <ul>
                <li>
                  In the situation where it is necessary to comply with subpoenas or when your actions violate the Membership Agreement
                </li>
                <li>
                  In which TDBA will buy or sell assets for the prospective seller or buyer
                </li>
                <li>
                  The necessity of exchange of information with other associations, organizations, and others for the sole purposes of fraud protection and credit risk reduction
                </li>
                <li>
                  In any circumstances that TDBA is required to follow any legal obligations, in order to reinforce and apply Membership Agreements, protect TDBA rights, property, consumers, and others.
